    <p>
      I'm Ricardo Lourenco, a Consulting Architect at Red Hat focused on Kubernetes, containers, OpenShift,
      and cloud-native infrastructure. I enjoy building reliable systems and automating operational workflows.
    </p>
    <p>
      My work involves designing and implementing Kubernetes operators, container security tooling,
      and platform engineering solutions. I'm particularly interested in the intersection of
      AI, developer experience, and infrastructure reliability.
    </p>
    <p>
      I hold an MSc in Artificial Intelligence, where my research focused on applying small language models
      to log anomaly detection and security monitoring. I write about what I learn on this blog.
    </p>
